    "summary": "According to a recent report, the National Examinations Council (NECO) has made it clear that there will be no extension for the 2026 Senior Secondary Certificate Examination (SSCE) registration. Schools are urged to adhere strictly to the registration deadlines to avoid any disruptions for candidates.",
    "fullContent": "According to the latest statement from the National Examinations Council (NECO), there will be no extensions granted for the registration of candidates for the 2026 Senior Secondary Certificate Examination (SSCE). Schools have been reminded that the deadline for normal registration is Monday, 25th May 2026, while late registration will end on Friday, 29th May 2026.\n\nThe council emphasized that schools must adhere strictly to these dates to ensure that all candidates are appropriately registered. This move comes as part of NECO's effort to streamline the examination process, ensuring a smooth and organized cycle for the upcoming SSCE.\n\nNECO's registrar has also highlighted that meeting these deadlines is essential for the proper administration of the exam. Failure to register within the specified periods could lead to students being excluded from sitting for the SSCE, potentially affecting their future academic opportunities, including university admissions and scholarship applications.\n\nThe warning stresses the importance of preparing early, as no further extensions will be granted, signaling NECO's commitment to maintaining a strict and efficient schedule for the 2026 examination cycle.",
